        <body>
            <div type="paratext">
                <p>
                    <span change="blue">
                        <hi rend="underline">[Page f.15r (from back of notebook)]</hi>
                    </span>
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="poetry">
                <head>[37] A Tribute to the memory of the Revd John Curwen</head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Yes! let the poor afflicted soul</l>
                    <l>The widow &amp; the orphan mourn!</l>
                    <l>Their stedfast friend, in death asleep,</l>
                    <l>Can soothe no more the heart forlorn</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>His was the candid generous soul &#8212;</l>
                    <l>The liberal hand, the kinder heart;</l>
                    <l>And never did a death-bell toll</l>
                    <l>For one more free from worldly art.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>And never was the cry of grief,</l>
                    <l>Disease, or poverty, or pain</l>
                    <l>Or supplication for relief</l>
                    <l>Addressed to his kind heart in vain.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>But ready still, by night or day</l>
                    <l>Was he the poor man&#8217;s prayer to hear,</l>
                    <l>The sufferer&#8217;s anguish to alloy</l>
                    <l>The desolate orphans heart to chear</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The cherished Friends who knew his work &#8212;</l>
                    <l>By firm esteem to him were bound</l> 
                </lg>    
                    <pb/>
            </div>
            
            <div type="paratext">
                <head>
                    <span change="blue">
                        <hi rend="underline">[Page 15v]</hi>
                    </span>
                </head>
            </div>
                
            <div type="poetry">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>And gaiety &amp; harmless mirth</l>
                    <l>In him a kind promoter found.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>His long descent &#8212; his ancient line &#8212;</l>
                    <l>Too oft in men the cause of pride &#8212;</l>
                    <l>He counted naugh! &#8212; his great design</l>
                    <l>Was to far nobler thoughts allied.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>It was the spread of Christian love</l>
                    <l>And charity &#8216;mongst small &amp; great;</l>
                    <l>His life long aim was to remove</l>
                    <l>Dissension, enmity, &amp; hate.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Although a carping few there be</l>
                    <l>Who slightingly his Merits hold;</l>
                    <l>Yet hundreds more will say with me</l>
                    <l>A warmer heart death ne&#8217;er made cold.</l>
                </lg>
                               
                <p rend="indent1">D Wordsworth. March 3<add rend="sup">rd</add> 1848</p>
               
            </div>
